{
  "stem": "1965.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 272.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the whole night they were working on my little body to make sure that I survive.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was very, very frightening experience.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because when your body is dehydrating like this, and in an atmosphere where you didn't have the tools to work with, somehow they found a way to keep me alive.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Madam Rothschild and several other people there who-- because you have to keep washing, and cleaning, and et cetera.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I also want to indicate that my brother, Sam-- I call him Sammy-- he was taken away-- both my brothers-- after three months staying with Madam Rothschild-- were separated from me and then from each other.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sammy was taken to a place known as Wezembeek.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was a very large place-- one building-- of which there were a little over 100 children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They used to go to school there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Germans came and forcibly closed the school and told them that they must go to the Catholic school.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they had to wear the khaki-- how do you say that-- cape-- with the yellow star, which I did likewise.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I wore also klompen-- the wooden shoes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they had to march 30 minutes each day to that school to be able to have some kind of education.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But then something happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They had to close the whole home, because the Gestapo was ready to take the children away.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You see, the underground was always working to make sure that all of us knew beforehand if we could stay in a place or not stay in a place.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So when-- when that happened, they closed the home, and non-Jewish Belgium women started to help in the Jewish underground to organize small groups of children, to place them in different homes, temporarily, to hide them.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
